SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1146
By Watson
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Chad Allen Young of
Ooltewah.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the untimely passing of Chad Allen Young of Ooltewah; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Young was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, known affectionately by many as "Trooper" or "Cheeseburger," Chad Young
was born on January 30, 1972, in Chattanooga; he attended Standifer Gap SDA School and
graduated from Ooltewah High School in 1990; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Young devoted twenty-three years of his life to serving his community
as a deputy in the Civil Warrants Unit with the Hamilton County Sheriff's Office, a role that was
not simply a career but a calling that he deeply loved and a part of who he was; and
WHEREAS, he took great pride in wearing the badge, upholding the law, and serving
others with unwavering dedication; and
WHEREAS, prior to his career in law enforcement, he worked as a corrections officer at
Walker State Prison and at Hays State Prison in Georgia; and
WHEREAS, throughout his years of service, Chad Young was known for his strong
sense of responsibility, his respect for others, and his steadfast desire to make a meaningful
difference in the lives of those he served; and
WHEREAS, a man of deep faith, Chad Young was a member of the Seventh-day
Adventist Church; and
SJR1146
017654
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mr. Young's favorite pastimes were playing online video games and
collecting firearms, and he also had a passion for muscle cars and hot rods; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to his family, Chad Young always endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Young is survived by his loving wife, Janet Young; mother, Jan (Don)
Grant; fur baby, Gigi; and half-brother and sister, Kanaan and Karryelle; and
WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his father, Jerry Allen Young, and his
grandparents, Jim and Irene Lovell and Jesse and Mildred Young; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Young will be remembered for his warmth, his humor, and the deep love
he shared with family and friends; and
WHEREAS, Chad Young leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in
public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should remember the
bountiful life of this exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Chad Allen Young,
reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and his stalwart commitment to living the
examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mr. Young.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
